caption: Great food
The food was sooooooooo salty!!! The waiter inattentive. Will not be returning ever again.  Go somewhere else...

The food is great, the staff is wonderful and welcoming, and it is very comfortable. They also have outside table heaters which is nice for outside seating. The half chicken was delicious, perfectly cooked and seasoned, and the mushroom side was also delicious.

The place is inviting, the service is decent, can be a bit slow due to short staffed which is understandable. The food is a hit or missed, Overall the place is average but I do think is a bit too pricey for what you get.  Also has one of the highest Covid surcharge fees.  Probably a place for an occasion but not a typical neighborhood place to dine in constantly
Great food and drinks. COVID procedures followed and made it comfortable to dine.
Always have loved the "Palace", I am 47 now; and, it was my Father who introduced me to this place, more than 3 decades ago.
My favorite mom and pop in the city! my kids love their pizza, there’s never a slice left
This is the best pizza rib and chicken restaurant in town.
The employees are always nice and have the best food.
First time ordering. Pizza was great! One of my new favorite places!
Their pizza is good and the shrimp is great cause it has no tails!!
I absolutely love their crust! So warm and soft with a nice crisp outer layer.
We had a pandemic-appropriate lovely dinner outside at a fireplace table. Food was delicious and our waiter James was outstanding and very friendly.
Great warm cocktails and fire tables. The perfect place for a socially distant meal this winter! Must order the scallops!
It is a very good place to have a good time and enjoy yourself

Sociale is the BEST neighborhood spot in the South Loop. I have never tried something I didnt like. The white sangria and chocolate hazelnut donuts are amazing, along with the burrata and any of the wood fired flatbreads. Patio seating is great in the summertime.

I live in the neighborhood and thought I’d give this place a try for some drinks and small plates. While there were some hiccups the first time we came, we gave it another shot and everything was amazing the second time around! It definitely says a lot about a local business when they want to keep you coming back.  I would recommend the sangria as well as the scallops and elotes!! Can’t wait to stop in again!

I visited this spot on a Sunday for brunch. It was pretty empty, so the environment was comfortable and relaxed. The food and drinks service was quick and our server was patient and ready to offer suggestions on the menu. I had the Almond Crusted French Toast. The presentation was great, however, the smoked caramel tasted much like bacon, which I did not like. My friends had cocktails, which were very strong and because I was looking to drink something lighter, the server offered to have a mimosa prepared. Overall the service was great and I would recommend to friends with more creative palettes and strong stomachs, but this place was not for me.
Had a meat and cheese board and margaritas.
1st time..Nice atmosphere..very good food!! Crab cakes & smoke bbq chicken wings..delicious..will visit again for sure!!!

We've been coming here for years. We always order the wood fired half chicken. The chicken was dry, over cooked, much smaller than it used to be, and no potatoes come with the dish anymore.  The price went up, and there is a PPE surcharge. The PPE I understand.  I am a restaurant owner. Times are tough. But don't raise prices, make your dishes smaller and less appetizing,  AND charge a PPE. One or the other. We are so disappointed and dissatisfied,  I can't see returning unless there is a change. I am not one to complain,  but wow. You had a great thing going, but you have really taken a turn.
Love it, great staff!
Food is overpriced and very bland.
Amazing
Indoor and patio seating. Food was excellent and the service was top shelf.

Okay food, service and atmosphere.  We ordered a couple of dishes to share, most looked good, but were small and just okay. I liked the grilled eggplant ($10 for a small 3 slice dish), the wood roasted chicken ($14) and the crispy potatoes gratin ($10, not a real gratin). The spread with toasted pitta ($14), corn elotes ($10), margarita flatbread ($14) and the pickled heirloom beet salad ($12) weren't to my liking. We also ordered the little doughnuts ($10) and bread pudding ($10, not a real bread pudding) which were disappointing.  The service was slow at times, but nice and warm. In terms of Covid-19 the waiters wear gloves and masks. They do ask customers to wear their masks when they deliver/take plates to/off the table, but they don't always enforce it.  Last thing: I never appreciate a cancellation fee. They hold us to $125 in case we didn't show up (that was especially weird since we reserved the table an hour before and the restaurant was pretty empty). On top of that they added $2.5 PPE fee for each person (why should customers pay for that?).
Nice cocktails ... delicious food 😋
Best place ever. Having my birthday there. Sociale forever, heaven sent. ;)
This was my third try for this location and glad we did it! I had not had a great experience either of my first two visits, but the third time is a charm.
Service is terrible.   Food is mediocre.   Prices are high.  Beyond Covid. No reason to bother

Love love the food here. We had the shrimp and avocado apitizers, the duck flat bread, the skirt steak and brussel sprouts for dinner and the donuts for dessert. Everything was so flavorful and fresh. I would highly recommend this spot for dinner!!

I have been going to Sociale for years and is my favorite restaurant and bar in the City!  The staff from Owners to Cooks and everywhere in between (bartenders rock!) are the friendliest bunch in the city and their food is a place you could literally eat every single night and change up the origin.  Scallops are by and far my favorite, The Duck Hash Skillet is one of the best brunch items I have ever had and if you don't at least stop in for brunch once, you are missing out!  Top notch place in Chicago and truly a hidden gem of the City!  Great for an evening solo, meeting up with friends, or heading out for a date.  You literally cannot go wrong here!

Sociale Chicago is incredible! The food is not only delicious, it's also unique. Feta bechamel was just part of a dish! Come on! So good!! Oh they have a Banh Mi flat bread! I can't, it was amazing! Have the lamb meatballs and the spreads. Also the roast chicken is done perfectly.

If nothing else, come for the patio / garden during sunset for a chill and calm vibe. AND absolutely get the Vegan Vindaloo. I am NOT a strict vegan by any means, but this dish could convert me. Just incredible. This place reminds me of some of the great rustic farm to table places in Napa / Sonoma.
Lovely corner bar. Drinks are great. Food is not too bad. I stick to the small plates.
Lovely spot to grab breakfast/ dinner! I tried chilaquelas and was happy with my food!
Definitely one of the best brunch places I’ve ever been. The food is delicious and inexpensive. 5 stars!

We absolutely loved everything. The atmosphere was rustic, sitting outside on the patio just added to that feeling. Blake (our waiter) was fun and served us quickly, never had to ask for a refill! So much flavor in every bite! From Starters, Entree to dessert, everything was the right portions (even though we could have kept eating everything!)  As far as drinks, definitely recommend their margaritas! Can’t wait to go back!
Local neighborhood restaurant with outdoor dinning. Food and cocktails were average. Wouldn't go out of my way to eat here but good for a quick meal if you're in the area.
The Mussels are fantastic and so are the drinks. Wonderful servers great atmosphere.
My wife and I shared some tapas there and, to this day, we still rave about their scallops. MUST TRYYYY!
Amazing food 👌
Good food, a little pricey for the portion size.
Did not enjoy the tapas food...Greek meatballs and chix wings had no flavor. Had an upset tummy later.
Great food even better service!
Service and food were delicious.
Delicious food and good service! The wait staff is very nice. We have been here several times and always have a good experience. Our favorites are the sumac-crusted scallops and the flatbreads.
Exceptional food, very welcoming employees, consistently good vibes. They charge convenient rates and the food quality is very good. Kudos.
Amazing food and great bar area to hang out with friends. They offer small dish which is enough to be full at reasonable price.
Great experience with friendly staff. Good conversation
Nice venue with the coolest staff!

Recently had a pleasant brunch at Sociale. They had a decent range of offerings on the menu, including classic brunch dishes, sandwiches, burgers, and salads, and we ended up getting walnut arugula salad and steak and eggs. The food was well-made and service was good but didn't stand out for me, especially in comparison with other brunch restaurants in the area. I felt that the portions were just a tad small (didn't leave feeling very full), but I think for the price point I was satisfied. I'd come back and try out small plates/dinner for sure another time.
Yummy food, good service
Limited menu, and the taste is okay, nothing great

We have started visiting every Sunday and it was our first time ordering food today. We ordered the Duck Confit and I just have to say, It was definitely not ones traditional flatbread. So , I must say..... You have to Try it. It had all these flavors that came together and made you appreciate the duck taste. With  great service from Matt(one of the bartenders) if you past by this place and your looking to have a drink and snacks.
$20 bottomless with Campo Viejo Cava which is decent Cava. Also the orange juice is delicious. I had the ChoriPan omelette which was very tasty. The smashed potatoes are great.

First time eating in at this establishment. I was extremely impressed with the food. The staff was phenomenal and Christine made my day ! I will definitely be going back numerous times primarily because of the amazing customer service Christine gave me and my party. The presentation of the Pork Belly was utterly masterful. Compliments to the chef ! 🤠🤙 Thank you for such a wonderful experience everyone.
Loved it! Great food and service
The service is great the people are nice, the food just doesn’t measure up. All the food I’ve had just wasn’t amazing especially when half sour is right across the street...
food: perfect. bar: ditto.
Fantastic array of food. Dishes are thoughtfully prepared to give a great tasteful experience. Such great food! Clean  bright and knowledgeable about the menu.
This hidden spot is located in South Loop’s Printers Row. The food is very good. Chefs are always cooking up fresh dishes from scratch.
Best brunch!!
This is excellent! Highly recommend!!

I love the atmosphere especially during warm months when the seating extends out to the sidewalks.  It's a busy intersection, but that definitely doesn't ruin the outdoor experience in this lively, family friendly, and multicultural neighborhood.  I like the variety of small plates and I don't think we've ever ordered a dish that was disappointing.

It was a last minute decision to come here for an early dinner before going to see a movie at the Roosevelt Collection.  The restaurant was relatively empty but we had made reservations on Open Table just in case.  The service was great.  I told our waitress that I am gluten and dairy intolerant.  She immediately went back to the kitchen to have the chef help her mark out on the menu what items I could eat (or could be made GF).  I ordered the seared scallops and tamarind mussels.  My boyfriend ordered the burger, short rib and skirt steak which was way too much food.  The mussels were the best I've had! I loved the sweet and sour flavors....however the waitress told us that the chef was going to change up his recipe for the mussels in the near future! :(  All our dishes were amazing. I don't know why we haven't come here before.  Street parking can be tough depending on what time of day you go.
Great food. Great product. Great service
Slow seevice

When we walked in we were informed that it was last call for food.  We decided on our meal quickly and then waited 15 minutes for them to take our order.  A little annoying, I didn't complain, but they must have noticed that they forgot about us.  After that it got better. Service was very attentive.  The heirloom beet salad was delicious and so were the scallops (but you only get 2).  The whiskey drink on the menu was also good. We enjoyed the background music and atmosphere.

Filthy bathroom Glass doors on wine cabinet filthy Corrugated boxes randomly on the floor Cook behind open window topping salads with his BARE HANDS made me sick.. need a visit from the health department
Nice vibe, chill, broad menu with great food. Good wine and drink selection. Indoor/outdoor seating is great particularly when the weather is nice.
Delicious!!!  Visit soon before the weather closes the NANA Walls!!!
I've been 3-4 times and had a good experience every time. It's a little pricey but everything I've tried has been very good. Great cocktails, too.

They charged me TWICE on my card. Everything seems ok till I went home and checked my bank account. We ended up paying 30+ more for the meal!!! The waitress didn’t tell me anything, which is very unfortunate. Anyways BE AWARE!!!! called my bank today to see if I can get my money back.

The service here was excellent, but the food was nothing to write home about it. The flatbread was like catching a mouthful of flour with each bite and the harissa root veggies on the chicken skewers were seasoned too heavily. The chicken itself was excellent and the chicken salad was also very refreshing.
Nice!
The late night dinner hit the spot! Try the meatballs, yummy!! Only downside, the plates are small.

I have been coming here for almost 2 Years Consistently!  I live around the Corner so I Visit often, I have never had a bad meal or Service!!  I am very     specific on what I want and have always been treated well, they are very good at making me happy and I have not been disappointed at all!!!!  Blake the bartender on Sundays is Very Charming and So very nice!!!  Come Visit for Brunch on Sunday’s, $20 bottomless mimosas, or Amazing dinner Options!!  You will not be disappointed!!!!  I Never am!!!  Thank You Sociale!!! 💋
The rain brought us here but we were so lucky it did. Everything we ordered was fantastic and the service was friendly and fast.

About $12-$15 per “small plate” if you’re into that sort of thing, but I just can’t justify the cost for a serving size fit for a rabbit or small rodent. Ended up costing my party of two just shy of $100 for dinner(without alcohol) and we still left hungry. Never again.
Disappointing food and service. Will not come again

Great place to have a afternoon drink or lunch, especially when is around the corner where you live. Super Friendly stuff and exceptional service. If you passing by and need a drink or something nice to eat, you would not be disappointed.
My new fav in the city!!! From brunch thru dinner... Perfection. No choice is bad!!!
Excellent food and cocktails!
The three stars are for the cute ambiance the food was awful I ordered some tuna sandwich on a croissant and the tuna and arugula was freezing cold. Hated every bite.
Good breakfast menu with some unique offerings like Duck Hash.  Try the French Toast of the day
Food smelled & looked AMAZING though didn't try it.  Drinks were great!

We were here to host a dinner event for a large group. The team at Sociale had everything planned perfectly and the food choices were outstanding and perfectly prepared. Wine pairings were spot on and scheduling was a breeze. I would definitely host a dinner here again.
Good tapas and service. But expensive for what you pay for.
Great brunch and half price bottles of wine on Sundays for the win!
Delicious seafood platter I ordered here was amazing... lots of vibrant flavor. Would recommend if you would like to treat your tastebuds

Had the scallops and salmon flat bread, both were delicious. Our waiter was nice and attentive. We got the black cherry mile and the Apple fritz and we're happy with both. I'm definitely going back to try more of the menu.
Simply superb. Loved everything I ordered.

Great location and perfect ambience for brunch. The food was good, but nothing outstanding. We went in on a Saturday morning when it was pretty empty but the service was a little slow since there was only one person handling all the tables.
Staff was polite, the building was very clean, and the food was amazing. If I wasn't from out of town, I'd definitely go there again.

Always pick Sociale ..awesome neighborhood restaurant/bar.....they've changed the menu since I was last here...they've added some entree items ... great food....creative cocktails along with an excellent wine list....great to sit on the sidewalk and enjoy a glass....caution...the Clark St side can be noisy.. the Polk side is best ..but not on a windy day.... effective service.. friendly staff...Martin..the everything guy..Amazing customer interaction...Steve...great personality..we had some good laughs...Natalie ...the bartender...Spectacular!...I look forward to the next time.
Perfect
Nice variety for Sunday Brunch, unique and traditional. Plus don't miss ordering a carafe of Mimosas.

This review is mainly for their guacamole & chips - SO GOOD! Besides that also had empanadas (pretty good), and a couple other tapas dishes that were a little too salty for my taste. Ambiance was great, would definitely come back for just drinks & guac/chips.

Amazing cocktails and small plates. Octopus with grapefruit, meatballs, tartare, mussels everything our server recommended was excellent. Go with their suggestions as the menu changes. Had an amazing time here!
Great food. The multiple course meal for $35 a person was more food than the four of us could finish. Staff is friendly service is great!

Over priced. There are several DELICIOUS small plated restaurants in Chicago that five you more for your buck. I would call their plates tiny overpriced plates. I was disappointed in the service. It took a long time for the server to check in once we got our food. We didn't have plates and there was no one to be seen so we had to grab plates from a table next to us. We then had to flag someone to pay after not being attended to. If you are hungry and in the area, go the the Japanese spot across the street. If you want small plates and are willing to travel a little, go check out Ema or the other hundreds of restaurants in Chicago that do it well. I won't be back to Sociale.
dropped in on tues. fast, efficient, and courteous service. the bill was appropriate.
Excellent service and delicious food. I had the French omelet which was divine.

Cool atmosphere - like a snazzy date or Ladies-Who-Lunch kinda place. Slightly on the pricey side - lunch with wine will cost you around $40 in the end, even with happy hour. Good service and good food - definitely loved the Brazilian seafood stew. However, beware going in groups of more than four as they do not do split checks and will only allow 3 cards max for payment which is annoying. Overall, worth a try once if in the area.

This is a great neighborhood establishment. Food is good, service is good, it’s kid friendly and they’ve always fit our big groups without hesitation. Awesome place, def recommend it. It is Tapas and I have been to other places but this has it’s own touch.

Great place for a group gathering. Easy going and accommodating staff. Delicious small plates. My favorites were the short ribs and pickled beet salad. The mohcian seafood stew was incredible. The chicken is a large enough to share among many people.

The food tasted great, but there was very little of it. This place definitely has it's customer base, but if you're spending this much just go to Korean/Japanese/American BBQ and get a delicious meal that leaves you actually satisfied.
Amazing food and drinks.

Came here on a Sunday day with some friends and was pleasantly surprised by the 1/2 bottle wine special. They even can cork and bag/seal the bottle if you don’t finish it, and you can take it home. Mostly small plates which came out fast, and were easy to share. Service was excellent and friendly, offering suggestions on drinks and food. Great neighborhood spot, with adults and families with kids alike.
I've never had chicken this good in my life.
Breakfast, brunch, lunch, or dinner Sociale comes through and delivers. I dare say that it is a staple at this time. Yum!
Priceless,, location,, staff was OK,, very pricey,,  nice place for high end Ppl..

Everything I had here was delicious. Would dine again.  Edit update: went a second time and the dishes are not consistent. The first time I went, everything was amazing and delicious. The 2nd a couple of things were. And the items that we got that were exactly the same as the first visit was disappointing. If this had been my first visit, I would not have gone again.
Awesome bar highly recommend
Cozy environment,  half chicken is the best.
Good breakfast choices. Ordered eggs overeasy. Arrived over cooked.

atmosphere was great but I wasn't too happy with my meal this time around. I've been here before and was excited to try the different plates but their lunch menu is much different. the chicken sandwich was suggested to me and it was not as good as I had hoped.

FANTASTIC food! It's small, sharing plates, kinda tapas-style, and it's wonderful quality. My favorite is probably the scallops. The atmosphere is great for hanging out with a few friends or going on a date. Had a ton of fun, will definitely go back!
Love this place. Classy. Good selection of beverages.  Really nice food
Fun place for drinks and tapas. Good date spot with attractive interior and helpful service.
A bit cramped during the busy hours but a nice variety of different restaurants to choose from. The bar is very nice. I've only visited once but its worth checking out
Great Food. I can claim that this restaurant is superb.

Great place to hang out with friends! For both times that I went, there were only a few tables taken on the weekends. Staff is great. I had Sociale Benedict, which was very heavy. I would not recommend it to people who wants something lighter for brunch.
Blueberry Lemon Pancakes 🤤
I only come here for 1 thing: The spicy margarita. SO GOOD

Bad service, OK food. Came for brunch and the place was nearly empty. Had to wait 45 minutes for our food and were told afterwards that the kitchen was short staffed. The waiter said he’d take a discount off our food. Remember that.  We had the cheesecake French toast which was dry with basically no cream cheese. The biscuits and gravy were good.  When the check came, there was no discount for the long wait. When I mentioned something, the waiter pretended he never said there’d be a discount.  Will not be coming back, and would not recommend you go either.

Ate here tonight with Natalee as our server. We decided to take the leap of faith and did the win pairing & tasting menu- we had 8 AMAZING dishes- every single thing we had was followed by a “oh my god” after the first bite. It was one fantastic thing after another. I highly recommend this restaurant and Natalee as a server- she was exquisite!

Less than average service.  Bartender did not put our drinks on coasters or a napkin.  I grabbed couple napkins...2nd drink she put on the counter next to the empty napkin.  $$$$ for what we received.
Nice place and staff, but, sadly, food is not up to the hype.
Great food, friendly service, and beautiful outdoor patio is great addition to the interior.

A nice patio and small-ish menu of dishes ranging from Cuban inspired sandwiches to falafel plus a few salads and "international" entres. This place doesn't quite have an identity, though I think it's meant to be tapas, but in this case there's not enough on the menu and dishes aren't plated in a manner (or portions) for sharing. It's just lacking a little flair and flavor despite a tempting sounding small menu. All things said and done, it's a simple place with fresh ingredients with some reasonably priced dishes. The sandwich I had once for lunch had inedible pieces of chicken fat while part of my friend's order was never brought until we asked a second time. It's conveniently located near the Harrison L stop and has a comfortable atmosphere so long as the volume on the tv's are off. A large bar area with a full drink menu. Reasonably priced.
Great tapas place. Good happy hour and drink selections, very knowledgeable staff. Definitely give this place a try.
Good food. Nice presentation. Rude service.
Great happy hour and service!
Visiting from Indy. Nice atmosphere. Small menu. I had the falafel burger and my spouse had the chicken& biscuits. The falafel wasnt the best...😒The service was great. Nothing to rave about. 🤷🏽‍♀️
Really good brunch selection
Lemons Blueberry Pancakes 😋😋😋😋😁🤗
Superslow service. Bland food They dont have whipped cream.
Great atmosphere! Great place to go with friends.
Can’t really rate the food since my daughter and I were ignored for 20 minutes while newer guests were served...so I’ll give the service 0 stars...We’ll find a place where we’re welcome instead.
Great place to socialize
Atmosphere was great. The Spicy Margarita is a must try!
Excellent cocktails
My favorite south loop spot for cocktails and small plates. One of the best happy hours in the city for high quality drinks and snacks.

Best tasting menu with complex flavors delivered in a no fuss simple and rustic environment. Make sure to try the flank steak, octopus, burrata, and the fresh beignets. The staff read friendly and food delicious and really affordable at $35/person. Highly recommended.

I really started enjoying Sociale more and more of the last couple of weeks.  Their happy hour has become one of my favorite go-to's.  A great drink selection, perfect bar bites and the servers make this a really good find.  Their is a ton of value in their happy hour so we'll continue to visit them not to mention if you're a Delta sky miles member you get 4 miles for every 1 dollar spent and then if you link your card to Yelp you get an additional 5-10% back.  Definitely worth it.
Great happy hour specials, sangria, cocktails, beer. Nice outdoor patio. wonderful service.
Food was good, but way over-priced. Steak was over-cooked.

A surprise.  It was good and comfortable with a satisfactory wine list, not overly marked up. It was modern and clean and if i was looking for a regular haunt i would choose this place in a heart bit.  The menu is share plates and fairly standard gastro pub, but it was prepared well

Went here for lunch with the family. Service was pretty good from the fella with salt pepper hair and beard. I ordered the Cubano but preferred the burger we ordered for the girls. Wife got the falafel burger and was disappointed. The flavor was good, just the name seemed to imply something different. Our thought would be falafels halved and served in place of reg burger patty. Expected the crispy exterior typical of a falafel. Instead I'd describe it as a chick pea patty cooked on skillet with a very mushy interior. Again, tasted ok but texture was not what we expected from the name.
First time Saturday starting out my Birthday week hanging with one of my sisters. It's a great place and food was yum! Will be back!
Excellent neighborhood spot. Great for a summer cocktail

I am not sure if a review of Sociale can truly capture the absolute awesomeness of the Good Eats Group and their various restaurants. Martin and John (owners) had been catering events for me for almost 2 years when it came time to plan my rehearsal dinner for our wedding. In addition to being my caterer, my fiancé (now husband) and I have eaten at their other restaurants and loved their food, so we knew we could rely on them for a delicious rehearsal dinner. As luck would have it, our wedding took place only about 4 blocks away from Sociale and we were able to host an amazing rehearsal dinner for our wedding party and out of town guests! Our journey to planning the rehearsal began with Martin graciously inviting us into the restaurant to do a tasting of different wines and menu items that would be a good fit for a passed hors d'oeuvres reception of 40-50 people. The food and wine were amazing! Having planned several events with Good Eats, and other caterers, a general concern of mine is how an item will be presented to guests and consumed. Martin had a plan for each item that was easy to take off the serving platter and be eaten without a tremendous amount of effort or mess, while still having 2-4 bites of each. They were incredibly accommodating and allowed us to pull items from their other restaurant menus (Sono Wood Fired Pizza & Burger Bar). We shared with Martin about how my grandfather was a great fisherman and smoked his own whitefish, so Martin created a crostini topped with a smoked whitefish spread that truly rivaled my grandfather’s! For the actual dinner, Martin blocked out about half of the bar area for us, by their wine case, which allowed easy access for drinks for our guests and the food to come directly out of the kitchen at an appropriate temperature directly into our guests hands/mouths. Sociale set up a beautiful piece of polished wood for a cheese and charcuterie bar by the wine case. Our guests could not stop talking about how delicious all of the food was-- especially the smoked whitefish spread, the pork belly with kimchi, and the scallops with pistachio butter. Everyone equally loved the two desserts:  Brazilian bread pudding and chocolate panna cotta. Overall, it was such an amazing night that we decided to return to Sociale for brunch on the Sunday morning after our wedding!

I would give Sociale five stars if it weren’t for the way the current evening manager treats regulars who frequent multiple times per week. He is the only one who NEVER greets with a smile or a welcome. The rest of the hardworking staff managing long hours from days to nights, behind the bar and serving tables are exceptional, warm, and welcoming  and they are the reason we love having Sociale in our neighborhood. They are world class. Good Eats group needs to evaluate who they currently have in management during the evenings and how this person treats loyal customers and Sociale’s exceptional staff.
Creative, unique menu options. Not your run of the mill menu, which lends itself to awesomely creative dishes and your periodic misses. But good overall.
The food was good but expensive for what it is, service was friendly but slow.

I would go back for cocktails but I don't have to eat there again...nothing about the smell of restaurant enticed my appetite.  My meal, however nice it looks, was unnecessarily over-salted. The service was good.

This is a neighborhood place so I really want to like it but we've had pretty average experiences here. The cost doesn't really match up with the dining experience or food. There are better brunch options.

Drinks - Mango sangria was the best out of the red and the peach. If you like sweeter one, peach would be good too. Red was the strongest.  Appetizers - Wings was so good and soft, the meat just fell off from the bone!! Our table liked the eggplant spread alone with the toast.  Desserts - deconstructed cheesecake was quite weird, we didn't care for it. The donuts and the jams were so good though!!! Definitely need to try that!
Great place to share some delicious small bites and  tasty cocktails.
Great ambiance, friendly and knowledgeable staff, fabulous tapas.  Just a get place all around.
Nothing special
Gotta try the scallops and burger...delicious
Best Scallops in Chicago!!! Amazing service, we were treated with free mussels by the owner, which was very generous of him. Very friendly atmosphere. Perfect for date night or hang out with friends.
Half chicken, great atmosphere,very nice staff.
Not bad, but not great. The food tasted pretty good but left us wanting more. It suffices for a tapas place but I won't be going back.

So far as food and drink go, it's really hit or miss, but the cocktails are always a miss (and I haven't seen any craft beers on tap). They do well with the atmosphere, and the management is professional and neighborly. Yet, the menu, despite rotating offerings, consistently lacks a center, muddling Sociale's concept. It just makes it difficult to select a satisfying, if at all memorable, course. I've been there a few times and manage to always get one standout dish, but just one (noting that it's a tapas style place... kinda).

Really nice decor, interesting menu but the delivery fell short. Salt was seriously lacking in every small dish and the sauces were under-developed. The meal was saved by a delicious gelato dessert. The portions and prices were absolutely perfect.
Terrible food and terrible service. There’s a 7-Eleven close by with better frozen food and service.
Our plans changed and I'm very glad they did. I don't have anything to fault them for or quibble about. I'd love to return next time I'm near downtown Chicago.
Smaller plates, yet good quality.
Great appetizers!
Upscale place for formal sittings.
Great atmosphere and decently priced happy hour specials ($4-$8).

I have been coming here a lot since I moved to Printer's Row a year and a half ago.  I would recommend coming here either for happy hour from 4-6pm or for weekend brunch. During happy hour, they feature their 4-5-6 menu, which is currently $4 smashed potatoes, $5 chistorras, and $6 pork belly. And for drinks they offer $4 draft beers (they always have four on rotation at a time), $5 red or white sangria, and $6 Sociale Cocktails (I prefer the spicy margarita).  For brunch, the portions are normal size and they even offer bottomless mimosas for something like $18. My favorite brunch dish is probably the duck hash skillet.  Unfortunately, I don't recommend coming here for dinner unless you're trying to impress a date. Sociale's dishes are focused around small plates, so the portions are a little small to be worth full price.  Definitely give this place a try.The staff are very friendly, the managers are caring and hands-on, and the atmosphere is warm and inviting.
Staff was beyond amazing and kind. They were very attentive. Not the mention our octopus & scallops weee cooked so perfectly!! We will definitely return

Amazing restaurant.  Went with no reservation on a Saturday around 7pm and got in right away.  Surprisingly it  was pretty quite in the restaurant when we were seated but got busier as we ate.  Quite honestly I can't believe this place was not packed full with a line out the door.  The food was amazing and the service was outstanding.  Pickled Beet Salad was A M A Z I N G !!!  Fresh and cold.  "Spreads cold plate" was delicious and the half roasted chicken was juicy and seasoned nicely.  They said the chicken would be a 20 min wait but it didn't take that long, either way it was worth the small wait .  Mai Thais were top notch.

I will never eat here!  My niece had to go to the emergency room after having a bite of her meal at Sociale Chicago. Her mom specifically told the staff about her allergies but they didn't take the appropriate precautions. The manager was extremely rude and never offered an apology. They did however take money for the food that was never eaten!

If you or someone you care about have food allergies, don't come here. My husband, daughter and myself came for dinner yesterday at about 6:30pm. My 6 year old daughter is allergic to peanuts and tree nuts. We told the waiter of these allergens when we placed our order. The first item that arrived was a meat and cheese plate with toasted bread and no obvious nuts. My daughter ate half a slice of salami, a nibble of one piece of cheese and one piece of bread. Soon after she complained that she felt itchy and that her throat felt tight. A couple more items came out as well as our drinks but we told the waiter our daughter was having an allergic reaction and to cancel the remaining order. My husband paid $60 for a meal we didn't get to eat while I medicated my daughter then we went to the emergency room to manage her reaction. She received 2 more medications in the ER to stop the tightening in her throat. Then today I called Sociale to let them know there was definitely the presence of nuts in our food. The first manager I spoke to was apologetic and seemed to feel bad, but said another manager would call me later. The second manager called me, but I'm not sure why he chose to call. He didn't seem to care and told me that they already have a process in place to ensure cross contamination does not occur. Obviously, their process is flawed because my daughter had to go to the ER. In 6 years, my daughter has never had to go to an ER after eating at a restaurant-either restaurants accommodate her allergies or let us know they can't and we leave. Btw- our meal wasn't even comped.

Place is exquisite inside with full floor-to-ceiling wine chillers and a modern vibe. Food was OK; definitely not the best I've ever had. For those of you wondering: this is not your average restaurant. Expect to find fancy dining options on the menu and nothing more (they don't even have ranch dressing, so that should tell you something).  All-in-all, worth a stop if you enjoy fine dining and downtown life.

Will never spend a dollar here. I've seen dogs on their patio countless times but when I showed up for my reservation with my dog they were incredibly rude. They don't allow dogs "on the patio" but you can out them on the sidewalk which is not safe because it's separated by rope. They could easily get tangled with people or other dogs in an incredibly high traffic area. I've seen dogs on their patio all the time. I live over here and see it regularly. Asked the server when we got there where dogs could sit and she said anywhere. This rude manager then came out and told me she has to sit on the sidewalk outside of the chain or we would have to leave. Never ever had a manager be that rude to me in the past. Too bad too because this could have been a regular neighborhood spot for me. Not now!! I will make sure I tell everyone to avoid going here because of their anti dog feelings and rude manager.

It was a nice setting but the food is unbelievably costy with tiny portion. We ordered a sea scallop from the special menu for $12. 95. There were 4 slices of scallop, equal to one and a half regular size scallop. Finally, we also ordered a roasted carrots for $8.95. The waiter told us before ordering there were carrots about 4" long. When the dish came, we saw only four carrots, with only one that is about 3' big, the rest three were about 2", one was half burned and the rest two pieces were completely burned. So basically, one 3" carrot cost us $8.95.  It was unbelievable and not a pleasant experience.
